  "title": "Project Architect",
  "description": "<p>A Leading Real Estate Investment Group in Singapore is seeking a dedicated Project Architect with drive, commitment, and enthusiasm to join our team. This is an excellent opportunity to be part of the Group’s high-impact development projects and to contribute to our continued success.</p><p>70K ( per annum)<br />Attractive remuneration package which will commensurate with qualifications & experience.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p>Responsibilities:</p><p>Collaborate with stakeholders to define project scope, objectives and deliverables.</p><p>Engage confidently with internal and external stakeholders (consultants, contractors, operators) throughout the design development and construction phase to ensure timely\ncompletion of quality in both new built and A&A projects.</p><p>Manage procurement process which includes reviewing of tender packages, evaluating proposals, value engineering, and presentation of cost benefit analysis to stakeholders prior to the appointment of vendors.</p><p>Maintain an overview of project status, including budget planning, cost control, procurement lead time, construction progress, and stakeholder management.</p><p>Manage consultants, contractors and suppliers effectively to ensure that the project is completed according to specifications, quality standards, cost and time frame.</p><p>To manage design change, variation orders, progress payment, final account, project documentation and oversee authorities’ submissions to ensure approvals are obtained in accordance with the project timelines.</p><p>Requirements:</p><p>Degree in Architecture, Construction Management or equivalent.</p><p>Minimum 8-10 years of relevant working experience as a project manager in the field of Architectural Design and Interior Design. Experience in hospitality, shophouse and office developments are preferred.</p><p>Self-motivated, adaptable and able to solve problems. Good organization, strong interpersonal and communication skills are essential.</p>",
